{"source_key":"sha256-ea08d35f42d5530fbe92c80d4f5b27e9","record_index":475,"record_hash":"sha256:938b8417cbd5316ec3a45e70c0e3923942480935df518e46b718abc5e8693200","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:38:53.258Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: agent-trail.md\n@@\n This only works when `refs/meta/main` has actually been published to the public\n GitHub repository. Forge's existing `but-sync` flow pushes metadata to private\n code.storage workspace refs such as `refs/<client_id>/meta/*`; that does not\n make metadata available to URL-replacement reviewers. Agent Trail v1 assumes\n public metadata already exists and should show a missing-metadata state when it\n does not. Publishing metadata to GitHub can be a later GitButler/GitMeta\n distribution feature.\n+\n+Pierre/code.storage should be considered a remote caching and Git hosting layer,\n+not a replacement for local GitMeta materialization in v1. The current\n+`git-meta-lib` entry point is path/repository based: `Session::open(path)` opens\n+a `gix::Repository`, creates or reads `.git/git-meta.sqlite`, fetches/materializes\n+metadata refs into that local store, and reads values through\n+`SessionTargetHandle`. `but-agentlog` currently depends on that shape.\n+\n+That means Agent Trail still needs a server-side scratch/cache Git repository\n+with filesystem access before calling the NAPI projection API. The NAPI request\n+should pass a local `repoPath`, not raw remote bytes.\n+\n+Pierre may still be useful in front of that local repository:\n+\n+- If code.storage can import or mirror the public GitHub repository and exact\n+  `refs/meta/main`, Forge can fetch the metadata ref from Pierre instead of\n+  GitHub.\n+- If code.storage can provide a stable Git Smart HTTP remote with better\n+  caching/rate-limit behavior, the scratch repo can use that remote for the\n+  exact metadata fetch.\n+- If Pierre only has Forge's private Cloud workspace refs, those refs are not\n+  valid public Agent Trail input for v1.\n+\n+Do not parse GitMeta trees directly from code.storage file APIs in Forge for\n+v1. That would duplicate `git-meta-lib` materialization and `but-agentlog`\n+storage interpretation. A future lower-level `git-meta-lib` API could accept an\n+explicit object database or in-memory GitMeta source, but that is a separate\n+library-design project.\n \n Example local setup:\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:38:53.258Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}